programme.desc: With the latest information from Gina, the SEALs leave for Bosnia in the next step on their mission to either seize or kill the Prince, who planned the attack on Rip.

programme.title: History Drama: Six S2E4
programme.desc: Gina offers Michael one last chance to disclose information on his connection with the Prince; Jackie becomes desperate while trying to protect her family.

programme.title: Car SOS S5E2
programme.desc: Petrol head Tony's Jaguar Mk2 has been in his family for over 40 years. Due to complications following a stomach operations he's not been able to restore the car himself and it's sat neglected in the garage for nearly two decades. With Fuzz battling to start the Jags engine and Tim having to get his hand dirty making parts it will be a race against time to get this British classic finished on time.

programme.title: China Relics Decoded E3
programme.desc: The rise of modern lifestyles in China has led to the explosion of the health and fitness industry, but this is far from new. Historian Sam Willis is on a journey to explore the health practices of the ancient Chinese. From the way they understood the body and its workings, to different traditions that developed to cure disease, Sam discovers how age-old concepts still loom large in the nation today.

programme.title: The Happenings E1
programme.desc: Barry and Stuart arrive in the quiet town of Stamford in England. Their aim is to make the residents believe aliens have arrived. To convince the public that extraterrestrials have been watching them for years, they go undercover as filmmakers and paranormal researchers, and plan an alien abduction and work to convince residents that the extraterrestrials brainwashed their animals.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E8
programme.sub-title: Channing Tatum In The Mountains Of Norway
programme.desc: It's been five years since Channing Tatum first appeared on Running Wild, and he's back for more- this time in the wilds of Norway! Their journey kicks off by skydiving into brutal terrain where giant boulder fields and towering cliffs stand in the way of extraction. During their seven-mile trek, Bear tests Channing to see how far he's come as a survivor - from foraging for food to Navy SEAL style cold-water emersion training. Channing even learns the ancient art of trout tickling!

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E9
programme.desc: What makes a car worth a million Euros? The answer for Horacio Pagani is a supercar that perfectly blends art and engineering, that has unsurpassed power, performance and luxury, the finest possible raw materials and in which every single one of its 4700 components will be recognized as a work of art. This film tells the story of Pagani's successor to his world famous Zonda.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S1E4
programme.desc: In order to feed passengers 35,000 feet up in the air, there's an army of chefs on the ground in the mega flight kitchens of TajSATS Delhi dishing up over 22,000 meals a day - from Economy to First Class!

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E3
programme.desc: As a herd of massive fish hit the waters of North Carolina, the competition heats up between the Northern and Southern fleets. The curse of the Outer Banks strikes again for one of New England's best fisherman. And with the small quota driving up prices, one Northerner takes a gamble to try and nab a monster blue fin, while the smallest boat in the fleet struggles to land their biggest-ever catch.

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E5
programme.desc: A study of the methods used by Manuel Noriega to rise from poverty to become dictator of Panama for six tumultuous years in the 1980s. As Chief of Intelligence he was the most feared man in Panama. He developed connections inside and outside the country that made him rich, powerful, and a key ally of the US in the region, while also working for Fidel Castro and the Medellin drug cartel, among others.

programme.title: 100%: Planes
programme.desc: 100% Planes tells amazing aviation stories from around the world, featuring aircrafts from the smallest microlight to the biggest cargo plane, and everything in between. Circumnavigate the globe, travel to the most beautiful and exotic locations, and hear the stories of pilots flying the most interesting and unusual planes.

programme.title: The Story Of God With Morgan Freeman S3E1
programme.desc: Morgan Freeman delves into why many religious believers desire to see God in human form - and how that strengthens their faith. From a living Kumari Goddess in the mountains of Nepal, to the Crown of Thorns many Christians believe was worn by Jesus during the crucifixion, Morgan will discover that these tangible connections help people make sense of the divine.

programme.title: Brain Games S6E3
programme.desc: Actor Anthony Anderson and his younger 'Black-ish' co-star Marsai Martin face off in a series of games with Keegan-Michael Key to explore the surprising differences between adults' and kids' brains. Challenges involve language, reflexes and reaction times, and risk-taking and mind control - all before the two co-stars face off in the Gauntlet's mental obstacle course. Plus, field correspondent Cara Santa Maria pits the driving skills of teens against those of adults by reversing the controls of a go-cart, using neuroscience to explain why one group performs much better than the other.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S1E5
programme.desc: What does it take to prepare over 10,000 meals a day for discerning clients of the Indian Railways and more? IRCTC shows you how it's done inside one of its central mega kitchens.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E7
programme.desc: The latest versions of the original pony car are built in Ford's Mustang Factory. Amazingly, both the cars and the factory are designed to produce 4 different models, from the base V6 to a 650HP fire breathing V8. In terms of horsepower, the 650HP V8 is the most powerful V8 built anywhere in the world.

programme.title: Notre Dame: Race Against The Inferno
programme.desc: On 15th April 2019, during Holy Monday Mass, the world's most famous cathedral caught fire. Notre-Dame de Paris was ablaze in minutes, as an epic battle unfolded for heroic French firefighters. Under the gaze of the world's media, they fought the inferno for more than 15 hours. Exclusive footage and interviews bring vividly to life the moment-by-moment courage of the Paris fire and police services, as they put their lives on the line to save this historic building.

programme.title: The Story Of God With Morgan Freeman S3E2
programme.desc: Morgan Freeman explores the role that the devil plays in various religions. From the ascetic monks in the Judean desert to the Buddhists of Nepal, he'll learn what purpose the figure of the devil serves. Is the devil a force of evil in the world that needs to be conquered? Or is it something that each one of us needs to conquer in our own heart?

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E6
programme.desc: A look at the techniques used by Idi Amin to rise from humble beginnings and build a powerful dictatorship in Uganda. Amin became an expert at deploying military force to achieve political power, a lesson he first learned from the British as a soldier in the colonial army. Through a combination of populist charm and brutal violence, backed up by a vast police state, Idi Amin managed to rule Uganda for eight years.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E7
programme.desc: The latest versions of the original pony car are built in Ford's Mustang Factory. Amazingly, both the cars and the factory are designed to produce 4 different models, from the base V6 to a 650HP fire breathing V8. programme.title: Nazi World War Weird E3
programme.desc: As the chaos of World War II engulfs Italy, a British officer discovers a 900 year old castle near the front line containing a vast collection of priceless artworks by some of Italy's greatest Renaissance masters. Hosts Dr. Sam Willis and Robert Joe are on site at Montegufoni Castle to get to the bottom of the tale.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E9
programme.desc: On-Air radio personality Bobby Bones joins Bear Grylls for the adventure of a lifetime in a massive Norwegian Fjord! A helicopter ride into the mountains is where their journey begins but from there, danger lurks at every turn - from giant rock domes and deadly bogs to raging rivers with currents strong enough to move cars. On top of that, the only way to reach their extraction is a 300-foot waterfall rappel that leaves even Bobby speechless!

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures: America's War E3
programme.desc: This is the story of Japan's final months of world war two. When America threatens to invade, the Japanese turn their country into a fortress and unleash a terrifying new weapon, suicide bombers. With surrender not an option, the Japanese prepare for the ultimate showdown on home soil. They plan to mobilise the entire country. Civilians must be ready to fight in hand-to-hand combat.

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E3
programme.desc: Gok Wan explores fusion food in Malaysia through a group of Chinese immigrants known as the Peranakans. His journey begins in the capital of Malaysia, Kuala Lumpur, where he learns the art of making Roti Jala, a Malay-style pancake made from a batter of coconut milk and turmeric. Gok's journey continues in producing his own Belachan, a shrimp sauce used in a fish curry.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E4
programme.desc: Doghouse fights to land a foul-hooked fish with a Hail Mary Harpoon shot, as the Northern fleet struggles to keep up with the Southern fleet. The Little Shell fishes hard to feed their growing families, and with a storm on the horizon, big risks can have serious consequences. And in a one Bluefin a day fishery, each captain must decide whether to roll the dice in bad weather or head in empty-handed.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S8E1
programme.desc: Susan Haglof moves to Egypt with her husband and adopts a newborn, named Marko. However Marko doesn't come with any papers and there is no proof that Susan is his adoptive mother. Hence she makes the decision to buy a birth certificate with her and her husband's name on it. Less than a year later, Susan is charged and facing jail time, however the worst is she may never see Marko again.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E11
programme.desc: Drain the Oceans solves one of the world's great mysteries - the identity of the Loch Ness Monster. Comparisons with the deepest lake on Earth - Lake Baikal in Russian Siberia, combined with military-grade scanning technology and a sonar curtain drawn across its entire surface - the plug is pulled on Scotland's famous loch. As the waters drain away, much more than a monster is revealed.

programme.title: Lawless Island Alaska Compilations S2E1
programme.desc: Long-time resident of Lawless Island, Gary Muelberger has seen it all. A fisherman. A trapper. His roots to Lawless Island are deep and his knowledge of how to subsistence live unmatched.

programme.title: Brain Games S6E4
programme.desc: Actress Rebel Wilson joins Keegan-Michael Key to explore the power of the subconscious when it comes to falling in love. Games and demos show how facial symmetry, color of clothing, vocal qualities, resemblance to family members and even a guitar case can play a role in attraction. Master mentalist Lior Suchard stuns Wilson by giving her details of a date she remembers - and pairs off potential partners who have a surprising thing in common - before Wilson takes on the Gauntlet, an obstacle course designed to test mental strength and agility.

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E4
programme.desc: Gok Wan explores Chinese food influenced by Dutch colonies in Amsterdam in this episode. He starts with the taste of indigenous local food which is called Boerenkool Stampot. A mixture of bacon, vegetables and mashed potatoes produces a fresh flavor for Gok. Then, Gok discovers a feast blended with Dutch, Indonesian, Chinese and Surinamese culture.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures: America's War E4
programme.desc: The extraordinary story of how Japan planned and carried out the surprise air attack on the US Navy in Hawaii. From Admiral Yamamoto's bold idea through months of secret preparation, pilot training, innovations in torpedo design, and clever ruses to deceive US military intelligence, culminating in a devastating strike on America's mighty Pacific Fleet on 7th December 1941.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E12
programme.desc: London is one of the most powerful cities on earth. Draining the Oceans reveals the story of the city's meteoric rise.

programme.title: Lawless Island Alaska Compilations S2E2
programme.desc: Lawless Island's Jack-of-all-trades is as sharp-witted as he is crafty. From his house to the gadgets and gizmos he's constructed along the way, he's found comfort in the wilds of Alaska.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S8E3
programme.desc: Unemployed Duane Wollum succumbs to the easy money involved in smuggling cocaine so he can support his daughter. With a package strapped to his body on his return to the US from Nicaragua, Duane is stopped for a routine check at the airport. Suddenly, people are diving for cover as Duane is surrounded with several rifles pointed at him.

programme.title: Jesus: Rise To Power E1
programme.desc: In his quest to find out about the rise of Christianity within the Roman Empire, Dr. Michael Scott uncovers how the Christian message spread and grew through Roman expertise and technology, how it became more visible and therefore more vulnerable to be attacked by the Roman authorities, and how it organized itself and broke away from its Jewish roots.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E12

programme.title: Dead End Express E1
programme.desc: In Idaho, jet boat pilot Brice Barnes responds to a Code-5 emergency message and must brave the Snake River by night to rescue a friend. Meanwhile, Alaskan bush pilot Rob Kinkade makes an emergency medicine drop to off-grid 'Wildman,' while horse packers Andy Breland and Chuck Allen rush a backup power supply to a fire spotter stranded alone on a mountaintop in Montana.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E10
programme.sub-title: Alex Honnold In The Swiss Alps
programme.desc: Free Solo rock-climber Alex Honnold joins Bear Grylls for a breathtaking adventure through the Swiss Alps! Alex is no stranger to dizzying heights, but he's not use to falling from them, so Bear kicks off the journey with a skydive into the jagged mountains. From there, it's a six-mile trek through craggy valleys and sheer cliffs where Bear teaches Alex how to survive the wild, but the tables turn when Alex takes Bear on a hair-raising climb!

programme.title: Scrapyard Supercar E3
programme.desc: Ralph and his 2 teams build scrap cars to face Shane's Audi R8 in a 0-60-0 face-off.

programme.title: Hidden Gems Of Turkey E3
programme.desc: National Geographic's Digital Nomad Andrew Evans completes his journey across Turkey in search of hidden gems by crossing the Bosphorus to the European side of Istanbul. Here, he immerses himself in the city's multicultural heritage, exploring how the city's unique location and complex history have shaped Istanbul today. Getting lost in its streets, he brings us a colourful picture of the city today.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E5
programme.desc: Bluefin Season in the Outer Banks of North Carolina is a struggle as sustainability imposes stricter limits on fishing. Northern tuna fisherman who followed the migration are blamed by Southern captains for siphoning their livelihood hurdling the competition into maximum overdrive in a race to catch the prized blue gold.

programme.title: Airport Security: Peru E9
programme.desc: On this episode, agents from the Antinarcotics Division of the Jorge Chavez Airport in Lima, Peru, must not only stop a woman trying to smuggle drugs in three different modalities, but also protect her life, as one of these modalities is extremely dangerous: she is carrying the drugs inside her vagina. In the meantime, a passenger shocks the agents by claiming he is a police informant, in an attempt to delay his judicial process. Later, officers will face the arduous task of inspecting an enormous shipment of contaminated capsules.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S19E2
programme.desc: A cargo jet plummets to earth in the Swedish Arctic. And as investigators pore over the evidence, a terrifying picture of chaos and confusion emerges.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E5
programme.desc: After abandoning his former home due to lack of resources, hunter-gatherer Matt journeys to the lower elevation canyons of southern Utah to find a new area to call home. He's hopeful this land will have the necessary resources he needs to survive the cold months. Winter has finally come, so Matt must work quickly to build a permanent shelter and protect himself from the elements.

programme.title: Brain Games S6E5
programme.desc: Actors and married couple Kristen Bell and Dax Shepard go head-to-head in the Battle of the Sexes, a series of games designed to find out how men's and women's brains differ. Challenges include stocking items in a fridge, communicating the details of a model's outfit and solving a math puzzle before a gas balloon explodes. Field correspondent Cara Santa Maria plays a game of telephone with a group in Los Angeles to see if men or women communicate better, and mentalist Lior Suchard astonishingly reveals the names of Bell and Shepard's first crushes, all culminating in the Gauntlet, a battle where the two compare their mental strength and agility.

programme.title: Japan: Between Earth And Sky E3
programme.desc: Japan is an archipelago of immeasurable natural wealth. The large southern islands, Shikoku, Kyushu and Okinawa, with their relaxed atmosphere, are the cradle of Japanese spirituality. Amid spectacular landscapes, this journey between sea and sky to discover the mystical and wild islands of the South will reveal the face of a secret Japan.

programme.title: Scrapyard Supercar E4
programme.desc: Ralph and his 2 teams build scrap cars to take on Shane's Chevrolet Camaro in a plane-pulling contest.

programme.title: Deadly Drops E1
programme.desc: DEADLY DROPS: EATEN BY AN ESCALATOR looks at the terrifying moments when these everyday machines suddenly cause chaos. Footage shows escalators spiraling out of control, of people being trapped, and even swallowed alive.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E6
programme.desc: Frontiersman Colbert sets up a trotline to catch fish while he works on his cabin. With spring quickly approaching, time is critical to get his cabin built before the mosquitoes arrive. While having Delia by his side has many advantages, it also means that woodsman Thorn needs to secure twice as many resources to survive.

programme.title: Airport Security: Peru E10
programme.desc: On this episode, agents of the Antinarcotics Division at the Jorge Chavez International Airport in Lima, Peru, are witnesses of a love betrayal. Officers detain a couple and find bottles of contaminated purple chicha in each of their suitcases. But the real shock comes during interrogation, as the boyfriend claims to be the sole perpetrator of this drug smuggling attempt, and confesses that he had brought his girlfriend to Peru under false pretenses. Then, a young man attempts to smuggle cocaine in food packages, while another young passenger carefully conceals narcotics in his clothes and a false bottom. Agents also inspect a package of hand-made garments that cannot be as harmless as it seems.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E17
programme.desc: Mokukchung is the cultural capital for the Ao Nagas. Aos is one of the major Naga tribes of Nagaland. As Pablo visits Mokokchung, he gets to witness the diversity of Nagas at the Moatsumung Festival. A colorful, spirited festival that brings together the entire Naga Community.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E1
programme.desc: Fish of the Day host Clarke Gayford joins Joe and Laura on ‘Big Blue' a 44ft Sailing Catamaran. Along the way he will jet boat up a river to a remote village, dive with huge bull sharks and track down local chef Lance Seeto to unlock an ancient local recipe.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E2
programme.desc: Fish of the Day host Clarke Gayford shows off his hometown of Gisborne. This includes hand feeding friendly wild stingrays and venturing out to his favourite fishing and diving spots trying to track down an unusual fish called a Pink Maomao. Along the way they encounter huge schools of Kingfish and a couple of friendly sharks.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E65
programme.desc: In the final episode Ben heads back down to his local, the Mersey Bluff Beach, here he creates a simple dish, using some wood roasted salmon. He checks out the Huon Salmon hatchery and has a chat with David Mitchell about their processes. At The University of Queensland Ben is joined by Professor Neena Mitter, who is aiming to change the game of growing avocados, together they make an avocado chutney full of flavour.

programme.title: Route Awakening S3E1
programme.desc: Dr Jonathan Clements, historian, author and TV host, meets a small community of the Dong tribe, one of China's 55 ethnic minority groups and participates in their unusual celebration of the mid-autumn festival, a ritual marking the last harvest of the year.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E2
programme.desc: Deep in Morocco's Middle Atlas Mountains, Chef Ramsay embarks on an epic adventure to unlock the secrets of the Berber cuisine.

programme.title: My Pacific Quest E3
programme.desc: Adventurer Ellis Emmett sets sail for the islands of Fiji, where he comes face to face with bull sharks, partakes in ancient Fijian fire walking rituals, and anchors in the remote Lau Islands, a beautiful place with a violent past.

programme.title: Get Lost In Korea
programme.desc: A photographer Greg Goodman teams up with Jesse Day, a Canadian rapper living in Seoul to discover the gems of Korea. They kick off their journey in Seoul to experience the night life. Then, they head to Shinan to dig mud for octopus and swallow it alive. After the fresh cuisine, they undergo rigorous training of Zen martial arts with the monks in Andong. It's a journey of humor and friendship!

programme.title: John Torode's Asia E1
programme.desc: Today's Asian adventure takes John Torode to Mumbai on the west coast of India. He begins his culinary exploration with a dusky guided tour of the street food served on Chowpatty Beach. Inspired by his cooking lessons and laden with produce from a visit to a local market, John undertakes a brand new dish of his own, Mango Samosas with a yogurt and mint dip. But are they any good?

programme.title: San Diego: More To Explore E2
programme.desc: Explore San Diego's many diverse offerings - from laid-back coastal towns to lively urban centers. Brimming with vibrant personalities and unique landscapes, San Diego has something for everyone.

programme.title: Hakka Renaissance E1
programme.desc: Historian anthropologist Julian Davison is teaming up with Natalie Pickles, host and model of British and Taiwanese descent. It's a journey of a lifetime for the unlikely duo as they traverse across Taiwan's north-western hinterlands, along a 150 km stretch of highway known as the Romantic Route 3. Meeting with local historian Chen Ban, they trace the footsteps of Hakka pioneers along a series of mountain trails that formed the backbone of their livelihood, transporting commodities and goods. Travelling further south, they get their hands dirty and learn how camphor, one of Taiwan's treasures is traditionally extracted. The duo also learn more about a tea that was created by the Hakka, that embodies the very spirit of what it means to be part of a ethnicity that were once outcasts.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E17
programme.desc: Mokukchung is the cultural capital for the Ao Nagas. Aos is one of the major Naga tribes of Nagaland. As Pablo visits Mokokchung, he gets to witness the diversity of Nagas at the Moatsumung Festival. A colorful, spirited festival that brings together the entire Naga Community.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E1
programme.desc: Fish of the Day host Clarke Gayford joins Joe and Laura on ‘Big Blue' a 44ft Sailing Catamaran. Along the way he will jet boat up a river to a remote village, dive with huge bull sharks and track down local chef Lance Seeto to unlock an ancient local recipe.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E2
programme.desc: Fish of the Day host Clarke Gayford shows off his hometown of Gisborne. This includes hand feeding friendly wild stingrays and venturing out to his favourite fishing and diving spots trying to track down an unusual fish called a Pink Maomao. Along the way they encounter huge schools of Kingfish and a couple of friendly sharks.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E65
programme.desc: In the final episode Ben heads back down to his local, the Mersey Bluff Beach, here he creates a simple dish, using some wood roasted salmon. He checks out the Huon Salmon hatchery and has a chat with David Mitchell about their processes. At The University of Queensland Ben is joined by Professor Neena Mitter, who is aiming to change the game of growing avocados, together they make an avocado chutney full of flavour.

programme.title: Route Awakening S3E1
programme.desc: Dr Jonathan Clements, historian, author and TV host, meets a small community of the Dong tribe, one of China's 55 ethnic minority groups and participates in their unusual celebration of the mid-autumn festival, a ritual marking the last harvest of the year.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E2
programme.desc: Deep in Morocco's Middle Atlas Mountains, Chef Ramsay embarks on an epic adventure to unlock the secrets of the Berber cuisine.

programme.title: My Pacific Quest E3
programme.desc: Adventurer Ellis Emmett sets sail for the islands of Fiji, where he comes face to face with bull sharks, partakes in ancient Fijian fire walking rituals, and anchors in the remote Lau Islands, a beautiful place with a violent past.

programme.title: Ugly House To Lovely House With George Clarke S2E1
programme.desc: In stunning rural Gloucestershire Simon and Lisa recently bought a carbuncle on the landscape. Originally built in the Dutch barn style this shoddy building was such a nightmare that neighbours compared it to the house in Amityville Horror. Simon hated it so much that he wanted to bulldoze it and start again. George teams the couple up with creative architect Laura Clark. Her challenge is to come up with a scheme to turn this terrifying building into a warm, welcoming, modern home, whilst still retaining some of its character. But with a limited budget and only 9 weeks to play with, Simon and Lisa may have to get their hands dirty if they want to achieve their dream.

programme.title: John Torode's Asia E2
programme.desc: John Torode is in the holy city of Amritsar in the Punjab region of northern India. His first outing takes him to the Golden Temple. What's remarkable about this site besides the temple itself is that it provides free meals to as many as 100,000 people per day, regardless of religion, colour or wealth.

programme.title: San Diego: More To Explore E3
programme.desc: San Diego is known for being on the cutting edge of scientific discovery. Whether that means saving an entire species from near extinction, to pushing the envelope on fine dining and rethinking how we utilize food. Host Robert Reid explores San Diego's smart advancements in technology and the inventive minds behind them.

programme.title: Hakka Renaissance E2
programme.desc: Historian anthropologist Julian Davison is teaming up with Natalie Pickles, host and model of British and Taiwanese descent, to explore and understand the relationship of Hakka food and their traditional lifestyle. The unlikely duo traverse across Taiwan's north-western hinterlands, along a 150 km stretch of highway known as the Romantic Route 3. Along the way, Julian and Natalie meet unique characters and learn that the heart of Hakka cuisine stemmed from their traditional way of living.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E18
programme.desc: Fermentation, Alcohol & beverages: Human migration led to the spread of amazing practices in many parts of the world. People migrated with the treasure of these practices and shared them with other races. Pablo learned more about this diverse country India as he dug through the practices in North East brought by people from countries like Tibet, Burma, Laos, Vietnam.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E3
programme.desc: Clarke travels to Aitutaki and catches up with Bonefish guide Etu, to catch one of the most challenging fish in the World to catch on Fly, the Bonefish. Along the way he catches up with the Prime Minister of the Cook Islands, also a keen fisherman and they head out to track down one of his favourite local fish the Kuta, for local Chef Thomas.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E4
programme.desc: Clarke enjoys a proper adventure off the East Coast of New Zealand taking a boat out to White Island, a very active volcano 50kms offhsore. Here conditions can quickly change. Catching his target fish after plenty of false alarms, Clarke takes it back to chef Josh in the local town of Whakatane. Josh specialises in celiac friendly quisine and his Hapuku dish does not dissapoint.

programme.title: Places We Go S8E1
programme.desc: Jen discovers the incredible treasures of Cambodia including Angkor Wat as well as meeting the most interesting locals.

programme.title: Route Awakening S3E2
programme.desc: Dr Jonathan Clements, historian, author and TV host, continues his exploration of the Dong tribe and visits a village considered the living fossil of ancient traditions where he learns folk crafts from the elderly and witnesses an elaborate Dong style funeral.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E3
programme.desc: Chef Gordon Ramsay travels down the Mekong River in Laos, Southeast Asia on an adventure to unlock the secrets of its cuisine.

programme.title: Somewhere In China E6
programme.desc: Peter and Jeff Hutchens visit the capital city, Beijing. They seek to compare the new with the old, and nowhere is this more stark than in Beijing. They meet with a local punk band, play table tennis with a member of the Communist Youth League, and travel to Inner Mongolia, where life has remained relatively unchanged for centuries.

programme.title: Eat: The Story Of Food E6
programme.desc: What we eat and how we eat today has changed so much that our great grandparents would hardly recognize it. We spend less of our time on food than ever before. How did this happen and what does it mean? Guilty Pleasures explores modern food and its uneasy relationship between convenience and quality.

programme.title: Island Hunter E1
programme.desc: The Island Hunter season starts off in the beautiful and highly popular tourism hotspot; Bali. The host, Liesel Hlista embarks on a mission to understand how the Balinese blend hospitality with luxury. And this is a journey that takes place on land, underwater and even in the air! A soothing journey that finds ultra luxurious healing centers such as Como Shambhala amidst the lush jungles of Ubud - to a hands on cooking stint at the Balinese fusion restaurant Mozaic, to checking out true African style Safaris in the heart of Bali. Helicopter rides over volcanos and reef-rescuing innovative dive resorts. This is an adventure true to the Island Hunter style.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E4
programme.desc: David visits the Savoi Plantations managed and run by the Shetye family. It is over 200 years old and covers 100-acres, where they grow all manners of Indian fruits including coconut and mango as well as almost every spice under the sun. David cooks, eats and spends time with the Shetye family to learn about organic farming and what it truly means to live off the land.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E5
programme.desc: Kollam is a beautiful old seaport city in Kerala known for its breathtaking backwaters so scenic that you would think you were on the set of a movie when floating down the calm rivers through the dense foliage. David explores life in this verdant region by digging for clams, taking a tour down the river aboard a floating restaurant, and cooking for guests at a local hotel.

programme.title: Confucius Was A Foodie S3E1
programme.desc: This episode sees Christine learning firsthand the very challenging ‘how to' of harvesting sea salt in Thailand's dramatically beautiful salt fields. Cushing visits the area's most unusual market that is regularly disrupted by the Maeklong Railway going right through it's center!

programme.title: Around The World In 80 Dishes E2
programme.desc: At his first stop after London, Manu arrives in Dubai where he has lined up some work in exchange for accommodations. Manu is keen on the culinary experience in Dubai so he sets off to the spice souk, fish markets, and a local pastry kitchen before having an experience of a lifetime in the desert, with food never far from the scene. Then it's onto India and a challenging train journey.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E9
programme.desc: In the 24 hour build special George Clarke takes on the 600 year old legend of the Ty Unnos; a piece of Welsh folklore that claims that if you can build a house with four walls, a roof and have a fire burning in your hearth in less than a day, then that house and the ground beneath it is yours.

programme.title: Pond Stars E1
programme.desc: In the season opener, Greg and the crew work to install a giant pond for Tony and Shari, who want a larger home for their koi fish. Meanwhile, a client calls Greg to fix her current pond, but instead of fixing it, Greg transforms the bland backyard into a wild sanctuary. Working on their best to turn two backyards into entirely new ecosystems, the team races to get both projects done.

programme.title: Pond Stars E2
programme.desc: After long hours, some close calls and way too much grunt work, the new guy Chris is tasked to lead a complete backyard makeover for his own company's Marketing Manager, Tony, and he's ready to prove he can make the grade in the pond business. Meanwhile, Ed and Greg take a field trip to a nearby high school to construct a courtyard pond to be used as a perfect outdoor classroom.

programme.title: Island Hunter E2
programme.desc: An uncommon destination for a series that explores exotic tropical getaways. But this island nation has some of the most evocative landscapes that mother nature has to offer! And, host Liesel Hlista explores the charms of the emerald state in it's off-season. Questionable weather is no match for the bounty of eats and drinks that Ireland has on offer; the best oysters this side of the Atlantic, the birthplace of Guinness and of course, the home to Irish whiskey. Liesel explores ultra luxurious (and famous) celebrity getaways like Castle Leslie, goes hands on at the Dunbrody house with celebrity chef Kevin Dundon, and explores the Wild Atlantic way at the fishing estate Ballynahinch Castle. The best way to explore Ireland in the off-season, Island Hunter style!

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E6
programme.desc: The historic region of Fort Kochi boasts an unexpected blend of cultural influences of Chinese, Indian, Portuguese and British. It also happens to be one of the only places in India where you can eat beef. David goes on a hunt for good stuff, enjoying chili fried and dry-fried beef. He meets up with Chef Ajeeth of the famed Brunton Boatyard to continue the beef-themed adventure at his restaurant.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E7
programme.desc: The beautiful Chinese fishing nets are iconic tourist attractions along the coast of Kochi and David discovers that the fishermen who operate them are just as intriguing. In a true cultural exchange, they teach David how to work the nets while David cooks their catch of the day for them. Later, David visits the idyllic Kayal island retreat where the women workers catch fish using only their hands.

programme.title: Confucius Was A Foodie S3E2
programme.desc: Chinese cuisines use sugar very differently from Western cuisines, and Christine starts her comparison in Paris and Athens where she looks at how Westerners interpret ‘sweet'. Traditionally, for the Chinese, sugar is predominantly used to achieve balance, but the liberal use of sugars in South East Asia Chinese cuisines are a culinary surprise.

programme.title: Around The World In 80 Dishes E3
programme.desc: Manu takes a short flight to Mumbai and for the first time in his life, he is in India. A feast for the senses, he wants to discover as much food as he can handle. He is referred to a local Idli maker in Dharavi, who agrees to teach him the craft of Idli-making. But language isn't the only barrier for Manu as he discovers the craziness of Dharavi and its people.

programme.desc: This is the final cruise for Captain Russo and he must have the Costa Serena in perfect running order before the handover to a new captain. There is also a new itinerary and a week of intensive safety tests keeping the crew busy before he disembarks. With a new route comes a change in the entertainment schedule as well. Preparations are in full swing for the final voyage of the season.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S8E1
programme.desc: George travels to Suffolk to meet Simon who wants to thank his mum Carole by converting a railway cattle carriage into a luxury mobile holiday home fit for a queen. George also meets Claire in East London who, having bought her dream vintage Morris Minor Caravanette discovers it's actually rotten to the core.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E5
programme.desc: Peter indulges his passion for seafood by diving for abalone, cooking up some local crayfish and curing trout with a delicious Margaret River gin.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E6
programme.desc: Peter completes his tour of Margaret River hosting a spectacular Beachside BBQ as part of the Gourmet Escape.

programme.title: Climbing The Property Ladder E2
programme.desc: Meet best friends Chris and Liz who have pooled their pension pots and bought their first renovation project in Preston. They aim to make a £19,000 profit in just four weeks, but with their schedule slipping, have they taken on more than they bargained for?

programme.title: Pond Stars E3
programme.desc: The Pond Stars head to the world-renowned Lincoln Park Zoo in downtown Chicago for two massive projects. First they come up with a solution to the Red Wolf exhibit whose pond has never functioned properly. While that's going on they also have a small rehab job to do on a water feature at the bird exhibit. What makes matters even harder is the Pond Stars have only 4 days to get it all done.

programme.title: Pond Stars E4
programme.desc: Greg and the team head to the sunshine state for two massive pond projects outside of Jacksonville, Florida. This first is to build one of the team's most challenging designs by completing a 30-foot pond and a 2,000-pound cypress bench. The Pond Stars then have to race the clock to design and install a new pond, patio and pergola in less than 48 hours.

programme.title: What's For Sale With A View S2E1
programme.desc: Simon dreams of waking up to a peaceful view, looking out over a still lake in perfect silence. A place to escape the constant hustle and noise of life as a busy developer where he and his kids are the only ones on their very own private lake.

programme.title: Places We Go S8E1
programme.desc: Jen discovers the incredible treasures of Cambodia including Angkor Wat as well as meeting the most interesting locals.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S1E1
programme.desc: Mat is beside himself with excitement at the possibility of creating fish tanks for the home plate backstop of the new Miami Marlins baseball stadium. However, Jose can't get back on track with his production schedule and an overlooked design flaw in the Marlins reefs could botch the delivery date. Will they be able to create tanks that will safely house the fish in the Marlin ballpark?

programme.title: World's Deadliest S2E3
programme.desc: Whether it's to hunt or to protect itself against predators, there are spine-chilling killing machines ready to mutate in surprising and amazing ways. From color changing to shape shifting, getting fierce, turning up the heat, fooling their prey or simply letting it fly, these animals will do anything it takes to survive on World's Deadliest: Transformers.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E5
programme.desc: Sioux comes face-to-face with a Green mamba, Simon is almost bitten by a Black mamba and they catch two bizarre snakes that don't belong in Durban!

programme.title: World's Deadliest (2019) E1
programme.desc: Carnivores are designed to kill so what happens when the deadliest go head to head? Meerkats fight in the deserts, a cuttlefish turns a reef into a warzone, a killer shrew wreaks havoc in the fields, baby alligators fight to survive the deadly swamp, Lions take on hyenas and tigers take on each other as carnivores battle each other to survive Nature's eternal war.

programme.title: Wild Indonesia (2015) E1
programme.desc: On Indonesias eastern frontier lies an ancient world forged by fire. Isolated for thousands of years it is a land of extremes where creatures have evolved beyond recognition. Each habitat harbours a unique mix of the bold and the bizarre as Papuas lost worlds support one of the richest and strangest concentrations of life on our planet.

programme.title: Wild Indonesia (2015) E2
programme.desc: Borneo is the worlds third largest island, and Sumatra is no dwarf in comparison. Both islands became cut off from the Asian mainland when sea levels rose at the end of the last ice age 12,000 years ago. Large animals became marooned, isolated from their mainland cousins. Over time, they have adapted and evolved to their new home developing an array of unique traits on each island. Today, these are the Islands of Monsters.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S1E2
programme.desc: Leaving Ben in charge of the warehouse, Mat takes off to the Caribbean island of Curacao with Allan Marshall, who runs biological operations at the Florida Aquarium, to locate some deep sea fish for a new exhibit. Meanwhile, the guys in the warehouse are stretched to the limit as Mat has promised a repeat client a 3000-gallon aquarium in just three weeks!

programme.title: World's Deadliest S2E8
programme.desc: What's hungrier than a predator? The underdog that fights back. Even the king of the jungle can be a victim in the wild. Watch as aggressive cape buffaloes toss a lion like a rag doll, a gazelle gets loose from a cheetah's grip and charges at him, and a tiger shark looking for food becomes food for orcas. The only hierarchy in the animal kingdom that matters is the survival of the fittest.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S3E6
programme.desc: Snake catcher Simon Keys and Siouxsie Gillett's business poses life and death situations. Every capture of pythons has its dangers, from an almost fatal mamba attack to the risks of being buried under a collapsing house with a snake. They conquer their fear and cope with one the world's deadliest creatures.

programme.title: Lion Kingdom E1
programme.desc: The Glade is a paradise in the desiccated plains of Ruaha. Water is here all year round. This bounty spawns strange relationships, like the pact that exists between a baboon and a lion family who, against all natural instincts, live in harmony. But peace in the Glade is shattered when thousands of buffalo arrive to drink. They are followed by the biggest pride in all of Ruaha National Park, The Baobab pride. While the Baobab pride hunts the herd inside the Glade, another pride arrives on the scene. They are the Njaa - a pride of drifters - always following the buffalo herd.

programme.title: Dead By Dawn Compilations E1
programme.desc: Around the world, nighttime is a time of terror. In Indonesia, a bat struggles to climb past a vanguard of vipers to reach the safety of her colony. In Southern India, a mother bandicoot rat must outswim a cobra and crocodiles to find food for her babies. And in the rainforests of Costa Rica, darkness means a deadly free-for-all. Who will survive the horrors of night long enough to see the day, and who will be dead by dawn?

programme.title: Hooked S5E2
programme.desc: An angler is yanked overboard by a ten-foot blue shark, a fisherman dodges a flying marlin that misses him by a fraction of an inch, and two daring spear fishermen dive in shark-infested waters on a quest for a scientific breakthrough. We'll travel to one of the most remote fishing grounds on Earth for death-defying confrontations of man and beast.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S1E5
programme.desc: Mat gets a call from a high-profile recording studio in Las Vegas with a tank that has aged prematurely and is due for a major aquatic overhaul. The studio caters to famed artists like Lady Gaga and Wayne Newton so the team's work will be seen by VIPs year round. Meanwhile, Francis is busy fact finding information on a nurse shark that needs to be relocated quickly.

programme.title: World's Deadliest S2E4
programme.desc: Welcome to the deadly world of the most armed and dangerous gangsters, assassins, and con artists of the animal kingdom. Be surrounded by a gang of flesh-eating fish taking down a river rat, a Bengal tiger showing how to get the job done alone, and a pack of killer whales living up to their name... then you will understand how these animals earned their spot on Nature's Most Wanted.

programme.title: The Incredible Dr. Pol S5E1
programme.desc: Summer is in full swing in central Michigan and Pol Vet Services has revved up to meet the growing needs of their clients - from farm calls to clinic emergencies, Dr. Pol and crew are full speed ahead. But animals are not the only ones in need of Dr. Pol's attention, as he and Charles embark on a mission to fix up his vintage DMC DeLorean for the local car show. The car will have to wait though, as the Pol duo have the pedal to the metal en route to a serious emergency - Bow Tie, a beloved family cow has suffered an enormous prolapse after giving birth. The longer the uterus is out the more it swells, so time is of the essence if they are to save Bow Tie in this emergency farm call. While Dr. Pol and Charles have their hands full, Dr. Brenda is headed to Caryl Dairy where the situation is grim for a cow struggling to give birth. With zero progress made since Dr. Brenda's arrival, the focus shifts from delivering the calf to saving the mother. Dr. Brenda resorts to a last ditc.

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S4E5
programme.desc: A good friend keeps you company when you're in need. In this episode, we feature stories of a Hawaiian surfer who hangs ten with his pet pig, a blind woman who has a guide horse, and an immobilized cat that's protected by a dachshund.

programme.title: Wild Sri Lanka E1
programme.desc: The seas surrounding Sri Lanka boasts an incredible array of habitats, all full of life. Sri Lanka's seas tell us much about how the island came to be – the vast, slow forces that underpin the extraordinary diversity of the island we see today. They also tell the story of Sri Lanka's complex climate and the ancient roots of many of the species that inhabit the island today.

programme.title: The Pack E2
programme.desc: A single African Hunting Dog is a tough, agile predator. A pack of them is a singular force of nature, able to take on prey many times their size and strength. Travel to Umfolozi Game Reserve in South Africa, and uncover how allegiances are built, strategies planned and teamwork developed, turning these canines into an elite hunting unit.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E3
programme.desc: The team has been commissioned to revive a showcase aquarium. They must recreate a sea turtle's natural habitat, however, the tank's marine life including sharks and stingrays, cannot be removed from the premises so someone will have to swim with the carnivores. Next, one tough client wants three tanks in one, completed in a fraction of the time the crew allots for such complex projects.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S3E1
programme.desc: See what happens when the animal kingdom's biggest and craziest fighters go head-to-head. There's a fight between lionesses and a leopard in an African big cat showdown, and two brown bears battle it out for a prime salmon-fishing spot on an Alaskan river. In the deadly Sahara Desert, an infamous honey badger takes on two jackals to protect her son.

programme.title: The Incredible Dr. Pol S5E2
programme.desc: The Isabella County Fair is just around the corner - which means Dr. Pol, Dr. Emily and Dr. Brenda are busy treating fair animals, making sure they are in tiptop shape for competition. Dr. Pol and Charles start the day tending to a fair pig, whose future isn't looking so fair after all. Will Dr. Pol be able to get this prolapsed show pig back in shape? Across town, Dr. Emily's up to bat, with a cow named Toro - who's abdominal hernia seems to be more than a hiccup on the road to winning the blue ribbon. Now it's Dr. Brenda's turn - there are two horn-y things on the heads of steers, Big Ron and Hannah, preventing them from getting fair-side. When the gates open and the animals come rolling in - Doc Pol's the man the Isabella County Fair looks to, to make sure all of the 4H animals are healthy and ready to show. But just because Dr. Pol works at the fair, doesn't mean he can't have a little fun at the fair too!

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S4E6
programme.desc: Dogs are the main characters featured in this episode. You'll see a cheetah who's friends with a Rhodesian Ridgeback, and a couple of Dalmatians who're cuddle partners with a cat, and another unlikely friendship between a human and an animal: a Floridian veterinarian who's friends with a pig.

programme.title: Wild Cats Of India E1
programme.desc: India's big cats remain the soul of the Indian terrain - acting as charismatic ambassadors for the protection of their ecosystems. In Episode 1, watch the snow leopard guard his kill from an unrelenting red fox and follow the lives of the last surviving Asiatic lions of Gir. Using the latest camera technology, the lives of these Big Cats have been brought to our very homes in Episode 1!

programme.title: Japan's Wild Year
programme.desc: Japan is synonymous with crowded high tech cities. In fact around three-quarters of Japan is uninhabited forests, mountains and coast lines. Here a great diversity of wildlife ekes out an existence adapted to a country with great extremes of climate. From the tropics in the south to the sub-arctic climate of Hokkaido island. From the northernmost primates in the world, the snow monkeys, bears, giant hornets and the weird goat-antelope serow, to the iconic red-headed crane and the abundant cherry salmon, the life blood of Japanese rivers.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S1E6
programme.desc: After meeting with the head of biology for the Rainforest Cafe, Jim, who demands that the new coral reefs have to look exactly like how they would appear in nature, the Living Color team realizes that they have to be on their A-game to accomplish this job. Meanwhile, Francis must figure out a way to create a predator tank he wants without putting the other fish in jeopardy.

programme.title: World's Deadliest S1E1
programme.desc: Some of the deadliest predators in the animal kingdom owe their success to the fact that they don't kill alone. World's Deadliest dives into the world of group predation with a look at twelve different species that use teamwork to hunt more effectively than they otherwise would be able to alone. They rely on strategy, communication, and often a well-planned ambush to secure their next meal.

programme.title: Wild Untamed Brazil E1
programme.desc: The forest once stretched thousands of kilometres along the Brazilian coast, but even the remaining 7% is home to many remarkable animals and unique species like muriquis, bush dogs and blue manakins. Coatimundis are one of the comical-looking ones with long noses and banded tails. But appearances can be deceptive – coatis are extremely efficient hunters.

programme.title: World's Weirdest Compilations E1
programme.desc: A shambling hoard of zombies has invaded the airwaves, but they're nothing new. The animal world has been out-doing zombies since the beginning of time. In this episode, we go in search of nature's finest examples of zombie-like behavior.

programme.title: The World's Most Famous Tiger
programme.desc: Known as the Queen of Ranthambore, Machli is the most famous tiger in the world. The legendary tigress is a fearsome warrior known for her daring exploits. And she's the mother of an incredible four litters of cubs. She's survived longer than most tigers in the wild. Threatened by her own offspring, the aging Machli is now in jeopardy of losing her reign of the best territory inside India's Ranthambore National Park.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E2
programme.desc: Ben is too comfortable behind his desk at Living Color headquarters, so Mat assigns him the job of installing a pair of outsized fish tanks around a fireplace at the Reuss residence in Orlando. What seems like an ordinary job proves to be a challenge for Ben, as he must hone both his client relations and physical skills. Mat leaves for Chicago to work on a terrarium for a rare Panama Golden Frog.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S3E2
programme.desc: In an all-American big cat showdown, a bobcat and a lynx fight tooth and claw for territory. Spanish fighting bulls show exactly what it means to have fighting in your genes as they go head-to-head to be the leaders of their herd. In the Sonoran Desert, a meat-eating mouse takes on one of the biggest centipedes on earth in a fight to the death.

programme.title: Wild Peru: Fight For Life
programme.desc: From Amazon rainforests to coastal deserts, wild Peru is among the most diverse and deadly places on Earth, bursting with vibrant life and sudden death. It's a varied landscape filled with danger for its inhabitants, who range from the expected to the extraordinary. Penguins, sea lions, spectacled bears, pumas, sloths, macaws, piranha and giant river otters are among the species that struggle to survive - and the outcomes can be surprising.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S4E1
programme.desc: Snake-catchers Simon and Siouxsie rush across Snake City to capture Africa's largest cobra in a pool, a python gatecrashes a wedding and an enormous black mamba terrorizes a neighborhood.

programme.title: Freaks & Creeps E3
programme.desc: Lucy is in South Africa to see the enigmatic Freaky Five: cape vultures, sungazer girdled lizards, golden-brown baboon tarantulas, ground pangolins, and chacma baboons. These animals are all important to South Africans and their traditions but they have been overlooked for years. Now Lucy is on a mission to reveal the mysterious lives of those lesser-known creatures.

programme.title: World's Deadliest S2E1
programme.desc: In the animal kingdom there are covert assassins lurking in the shadows, ready to pounce at lightning speed to fight for survival and battle their foes. Possessing the skills to kill, these world's deadliest animals will use their jaw-dropping talents to fight to live another day. From stealthy cats to patient seals, giant centipedes to kick-boxing kangaroos, these are the Animal Ninja Warriors.

programme.title: Rude(Ish) Tube E18
programme.desc: Rude(ish) Tube is a hilarious half hour show featuring the funniest, freakiest and most incredible clips that have ever been uploaded to the World Wide Web featuring pranks, animals and cute kids.

programme.title: Blue Bloods S8E12
programme.desc: Season 8 premieres in a shocking twist, it was revealed that Danny Reagan's wife, ER nurse Linda (Amy Carlson), has passed on, having perished on May 28 in a helicopter crash.

programme.title: NCIS: Los Angeles S9E12
programme.desc: After napalm is detected at a crime scene, the NCIS team investigates the sole casualty for possible links to terrorism.

programme.title: Truck
programme.desc: Seorang sopir truk tak sengaja melihat pembunuhan oleh sebuah geng. Ia bersedia membantu membuang mayat-mayat itu agar tetap dibiarkan hidup. Namun, situasi memburuk ketika seorang pembunuh berantai menumpang truknya.

programme.title: Heung-boo: The Revolutionist
programme.desc: Sebuah sandiwara jalanan menjadi populer pada masa Dinasti Joseon. Heung-boo, sang penulis naskah, banyak diincar oleh para elit politik yang ingin menggunakan ketenarannya untuk kepentingan mereka sendiri.

programme.title: The Accidental Detective
programme.desc: Seorang penulis blog kriminal dan seorang detektif veteran bekerjasama demi membuktikan bahwa teman mereka tidak bersalah dan dijadikan kambing hitam atas pembunuhan nan keji.

programme.title: Love Guide For Dumpees
programme.desc: Dua orang yang baru saja dicampakkan menghabiskan malam dengan mabuk bersama untuk melupakan mantan mereka, lalu sepakat untuk bertemu sembilan kali lagi sebelum berjanji untuk tidak bertemu lagi.

programme.title: Wonderful Nightmare
programme.desc: Akibat kesalahan di surga, seorang pengacara nan tak percaya cinta tewas dalam kecelakaan mobil. Guna menutupi kesalahan mereka, ia harus hidup sebagai ibu rumah tangga selama sebulan demi kembali ke kehidupan lamanya.

programme.title: The Fatal Encounter
programme.desc: Raja Jeongjo diancam oleh faksi Nowon dan Soron yang menjadi lawannya dan berjuang untuk melindungi takhtanya. Ia menghadapi perlawanan dari segala arah dan menjadi target pembunuhan.

programme.title: Detective K: Virtuous Widow
programme.desc: Detektif top Joseon menyelidiki serangkaian pembunuhan misterius yang berkaitan dengan konspirasi besar yang dapat menggemparkan seluruh negeri.

programme.title: Detective K: The Living Dead
programme.desc: Detektif K dan rekannya dibantu seorang wanita penderita amnesia guna menguak suatu kasus pembunuhan. Mereka melihat gigitan vampir pada jasad para korban dan menyadari bahwa wanita itu terkait dengan kematian mereka.

programme.title: The Scam
programme.desc: Hyeon-Soo bergabung dengan tim elit yang dibentuk oleh seorang gangster yang menyamar menjadi seorang investor untuk melakukan penipuan terbesar demi mendapatkan 60.000.000 dolar dari pasar saham.

programme.title: I Am The King

programme.title: The Tooth And The Nail
